critical_positive: I really enjoyed how we were able to share our opinions openly and honestly without judging one another, and on some very potentially sensitive issues no less. I felt like I could have an open and intelligent conversation with my partner and share with her in ways I couldn't do with most other people. We may not have always agreed, but we did not try to belittle one another either, which was a refreshing change from so many other conversations with people, especially strangers.
critical_negative: We did both tend to interrupt each other a bit, I think myself a little worse, which probably detracted from the conversation a little. I could also hear myself echoing through her speakers which was a little distracting, although not enough to be that big of a deal. In addition, there was a little bit of a barrier with regard to her accent, which was a bit thick and difficult to understand at times. I could understand almost everything that she said, but not quite all, and I had to focus in on it a lot more to be able to understand.
